cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.MM

This paper is about real-time bidding (RTB) in online advertising, which involves the use of algorithms and data analysis to select and bid on ad impressions in real-time. This topic is closely related to several sub-fields of computer science, including information retrieval (cs.IR), machine learning (cs.LG), social and information networks (cs.SI), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and multimedia (cs.MM). Given the focus on modeling and predicting the performance lift of ads, as well as the use of blind A/B testing and attribution models, cs.IR and cs.LG are the most likely sub-categories. However, the paper also touches on issues related to data processing, optimization, and user behavior, which could be relevant to cs.SI, cs.DS, and cs.MM.
